Deadline class: Enhance alignment with coding standards
commitResults.messageBody:
The Deadline class has formatting inconsistencies and lacks clarity
in documentation. These issues reduce readability and make the code
less maintainable.

This commit improves the class by:
- Updating Javadoc comments for the constructor and toString method
  to make them more descriptive and aligned with coding standards.
- Ensuring consistent formatting, indentation, and layout to enhance
  readability.
- Refining method descriptions to comply with Java documentation
  standards.
- Adding a detailed explanation of the string representation format
  in the toString method.

These changes improve the readability and adherence to coding
standards of the Deadline class.

commitResults.messageTitle: Ui class: Enhance alignment with coding standards
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit improves the Ui class by addressing formatting
inconsistencies and unclear documentation.

Key updates include:
- Refining Javadoc comments for the constructor and methods
  to make them more descriptive and informative.
- Improve formatting, indentation, and layout to ensure consistency.
- Introduce a static final constant, LINE_SEPARATOR, to eliminate
  repetitive string literals and enhance code maintainability.

These changes make the Ui class easier to read, understand,
and maintain while more closely adhering to the Java coding standards.
